      • taxonName

        public static Query taxonName(String taxon)
        Create a query based on an NCBI taxonomy name. 

         Note: A taxonomic name can occur in different taxonomic nodes, e.g. Bacteria the superkingdom which as
 has an NCBI taxID of 2 and the Bacteria found at the genus level which has an NCBI id of 629395
        Parameters:
        taxon - name of the NCBI taxon
        Returns:
        Query

      • organismHostName

        public static Query organismHostName(String name)
        Creates a search query that will look for virus proteins that are present in the host being searched.

        As an example, searching for Macaca will return all proteins that are virus related and found in searched host.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the host carrying a virus
        Returns:
        Query

      • organismHostID

        public static Query organismHostID(int taxonomy)
        Creates a search query that will look for virus proteins that are present in the host being searched. The search takes as an argument the NCBI taxonomy name of the host

        As an example, searching for 9539 will return all proteins that are virus related and found in searched host.

        Parameters:
        taxonomy - int value representation of the taxonomy identifier
        Returns:
        Query

      • xref

        public static Query xref(DatabaseType dbType,
                         String value)
        Creates a query that matches entries containing a specified database cross-reference type, with the specified cross-reference value. For example, DatabaseType.GO and "exoribonuclease activity" would find entries whose gene ontology cross-references contain "exoribonuclease activity".
        Parameters:
        dbType - the database cross-reference DatabaseType to query on
        value - the cross-reference values to search for
        Returns:
        Query
        See Also:
        DatabaseType
